Makon daya bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani shafi hudu a wata jaridar Amurka da ke tallata fa'idodin cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafofin yada labarai na Amurka don yada farfaganda.
A ranar Laraba da ta gabata, Shugaba Donald Trump ya yi magana da wani mai biyan kuɗi na China Daily a The Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a jihar Iowa, bayan ya zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben da aka yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, wanda China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka bayyana wa Reuters cewa wani sabon mataki ne na yakin neman zaben Washington na kara matsa lamba kan kasar Sin.
Ko da yake al'ada ce ga gwamnatocin kasashen waje su sanya tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington suna cikin yakin kasuwanci da ke kara tsanantawa wanda ya ga karin haraji kan kayayyakin da ake shigowa da su.
An yi amfani da takunkumin da China ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya don hukunta masu fitar da kayayyaki daga jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, a cewar masana na China da na Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya yi ikirarin cewa Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni.
A cikin wani labari a cikin jaridar The Sunday, mai suna The Des Moines Register, Branstad ya rubuta cewa: "yana ƙara yawan cin zarafi ta hanyar buga tallace-tallace a cikin jaridarmu ta kyauta".
"A yada farfagandarsu, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi amfani da al'adar Amurka mai daraja na 'yancin faɗar albarkacin baki da kuma 'yancin jarida kyauta ta hanyar saka tallace-tallace da aka biya a cikin The Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A wani bangare kuma, a tashar tallace-tallace da ke kan tituna a nan birnin Beijing, za ku ga 'yan muryoyin da ba su jitu ba, kuma ba za ku ga ainihin ra'ayoyi masu banbanci da 'yan kasar Sin ke da su ba game da yanayin tattalin arzikin kasar Sin, saboda jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin ce ke mamaye kafofin watsa labarai", in ji shi.
Ya kara da cewa "daya daga cikin manyan jaridu a kasar Sin ya kauce wa tayin buga" labarin nasa, amma bai bayyana sunan littafin ba.
